[1] Saudi Arabia, 2 new cases - MOH 27 Oct 2014
Date: Mon 27 Oct 2014
Source: Saudi Arabia Ministry of Health [edited]
http://www.moh.gov.sa/en/ccc/pressreleases/pages/default.aspx


As of 12:00 noon on 27 Oct 2014:
Laboratory-confirmed cases of MERS-CoV infection: 779, including
Deaths: 331
Recovered cases: 433
Active cases: 15

Information on today's newly confirmed cases (2):
1- Riyadh: 61 year old Expat female, non-healthcare worker, currently admitted to ICU, history of pre-existing co-morbidities, no history of animal exposure, no history of contact with suspected or confirmed cases in hospitals/clinics, no history of contact with suspected or confirmed cases in the community.
2- Jeddah: 90 year old Saudi female, non-healthcare worker, currently admitted to ICU, history of pre-existing co-morbidities, no history of animal exposure or contact with suspected or confirmed cases in the community, currently under investigation for contact with suspected or confirmed cases in hospitals/clinics.

